excerpt: Bustling, colorful bazaar with stalls selling fresh produce, housewares, clothing & more.
detail_description: Mapusa Municipal Market, also known as Mapusa Friday Market, is a vibrant and bustling bazaar in the heart of Mapusa town in Goa. Open every day but busiest on Fridays, it offers a glimpse into authentic Goan culture and local life. Visitors can explore stalls selling a variety of items including fresh produce, spices, sweets, cashews, chillies, homemade fish fry, sausages, clothing and household goods.
name: Mapusa Municipal Market
address: Municipal Market, Mapusa, Goa 403507, India

excerpt: Built in 1705, the hilltop ruins of this Portuguese military fortress offer scenic views.
detail_description: Corjuem Fort, located in North Goa, is a historic Portuguese military fortress dating back to 1705. Despite its smaller size compared to other forts, it offers stunning panoramic views of the Corjuem River and surrounding landscapes. Originally built by Maratha rulers and later renovated by the Portuguese, this protected monument stands as a testament to Goa's rich history.
name: Corjuem Fort
address: Off, Road, Corjuem, Aldona, Goa 403508, India

detail_description: The Our Lady of Immaculate Conception Church, situated in Panjim, Goa, is a significant historical site and a spiritual haven. This iconic church, constructed in the 16th century and featuring Portuguese Baroque architecture, holds great cultural importance in Goan history. Overlooking the city of Panjim, it replaced an earlier chapel and now stands as a symbol of religious expansion during Portuguese colonial rule.
name: Our Lady of Immaculate Conception Church, Moira
address: JR2V+HVQ, Moide, Goa 403206, India

detail_description: Chapora, located in the northern part of Goa, is a picturesque river that eventually meets the Arabian Sea. This river offers opportunities for water sports like white river rafting and kayaking due to its perfect water current and rapids. The area is popular among nature lovers and casual swimmers, with the nearby fort serving as a sunset point for visitors. The region boasts Portuguese-style architectural houses and cool breezes, making it an ideal spot to spend holidays.
name: Chapora
address: Goa

excerpt: Mapusa is a city in North Goa, India. It is situated 13 km north of the state capital of Panaji. The city is the headquarters of Bardez taluka. It is located on the main highway NH-17, linking Mumbai to Kochi. During Portuguese India, the city was known as "Mapuçá". Wikipedia.
detail_description: Mapusa, also known as Mapuçá in Portuguese, is a charming town located 13 km north of Panaji, the capital of North Goa, India. It serves as the headquarters of Bardez Taluka and is conveniently situated on the NH-17 highway connecting Mumbai to Kochi.
name: Mapusa
address: Goa 403519, India

excerpt: Popular tourist beach providing activities such as parasailing, jet ski & banana boat rentals.
detail_description: Anjuna Beach, located in North Goa, is a popular destination known for its stunning natural beauty and white sandy shores. It offers a range of activities such as parasailing, jet skiing, banana boat rentals, bungee jumping from an 80-foot tower, paragliding, and windsurfing. The beach is famous for its full moon beach parties during New Year and Christmas and attracts both domestic and foreign tourists.
name: Anjuna Beach
address: Anjuna, Goa 403509, India

excerpt: 1612 Portuguese fortress offering ocean views & an abandoned lighthouse erected in 1864.
detail_description: Aguada Fort, a 1612 Portuguese fortress, offers stunning ocean views and features an abandoned lighthouse built in 1864. Visitors can unwind with ayurvedic massages or partake in various yoga classes available in Goa. For the more adventurous, water sports and cookery classes are also on offer. The fort is a great spot to climb up for breathtaking sunset views. Sinquerim Beach, the first tourist beach of North Goa, is nearby and close to Aguada Fort.
name: Fort Aguada
address: Fort Aguada Rd, Aguada Fort Area, Candolim, Goa 403515, India

excerpt: Framed by green hills & rock formations, this scenic beach has chairs, palapas & a relaxed vibe.
detail_description: Ozran Beach, located in North Goa, is a charming coastal retreat known for its pristine white sands and tranquil atmosphere. The beach is framed by lush green hills and rock formations, creating a picturesque setting for visitors to relax and unwind. Anjuna, often referred to as the jewel of Ozran, has been a popular destination since the 1960s and continues to attract an eclectic mix of tourists from around the world.
name: Ozran Beach
address: Anjuna, Goa 403519, India

excerpt: This modern, 3-story museum offers works by Indian & international artists, plus a cafe & gift shop.
detail_description: Museum of Goa, MOG, is a contemporary 3-story museum showcasing the works of Indian and international artists. It celebrates Goa's rich history, culture, and traditions through modern art. The museum features multiple galleries exhibiting sculptures, paintings, photography, installations, and moving images that reflect the fusion of Portuguese lifestyles with Goan culture. Visitors can also enjoy an on-site organic cafe, art store, and studio for artists to use.
name: Museum of Goa, MOG
address: 79, Estate, Pilerne Industrial Estates, Pilern, Goa 403511, India

excerpt: Compact waterpark featuring 5 small pools & a variety of slides, plus a shop & eatery.
detail_description: Splashdown Waterpark is a compact yet exciting water park located in Goa. It features 5 small pools and a variety of slides suitable for all ages. The park offers age-specific 4-storeyed slides, cannonball slides, leisure pools, adventure walks, lazy rivers, and more. Additionally, visitors can enjoy the convenience of an on-site shop and eatery.
name: Splashdown Waterpark

excerpt: Imposing Neo-Gothic Catholic church with grand spires & gilded interior ornamentation.
detail_description: The Mae De Deus Church, also known as Mother of Goa church, is a stunning Neo-Gothic Catholic church located in the serene area of Saligao in North Goa. This architectural gem was founded in 1588 A.D and rebuilt in 1739, showcasing an impressive blend of grand spires and gilded interior ornamentation. Visitors can admire its timeless charm and serenity while walking around the outside premises at any time, provided they are respectful and considerate.
name: Mae De Deus Church
address: GQWP+R47, Chogm Rd, Muddavaddi, Saligao, Goa 403511, India

detail_description: Raj Bhavan, located in Dona Paula near the beautiful Dona Paula Beach, is a colonial mansion showcasing stunning Portuguese architecture. Originally built as a fortress in the 16th century, it later became the residence for Portuguese viceroys and eventually served as a Governor's palace. Situated about 9 kilometers from Panjim, this historic site spans across 88 acres of land and features a large church called Lady of Cape.
name: Raj Bhavan
address: FQ7Q+7GJ, Raj Bhavan Road, Panaji, Dona Paula, Goa 403004, India

detail_description: Located in the lively streets of Goa, the AAA All About Alcohol Museum is a unique tribute to the world of alcohol. Housed in a colonial-era building, it showcases ancient distilling equipment and offers an immersive journey through the history and production of spirits. Divided into five rooms, visitors can explore various aspects of alcohol production from distillation to fumigation. The museum's curator, Mr. Armando, warmly welcomes guests and shares insights into the exhibits without pressuring anyone to drink.
name: AAA All About Alcohol Museum
address: Main Road, Candolim, Goa 403515, India
